subsection.def:
contributor
                    (供款人) means an officer to whom this Ordinance
                applies;

Directors
                    (委員會) means the Board of Directors
                established by section 4;

paragraph.continued:
if the requirement of minimum qualifying service had not been applicable
                    to him;
                    or

paragraph.content:
if his contributory service was less than 20 years but would not have been
                    for a period shorter than 20 years if he died or retired at the age of 55 years,
                    be computed as if his contributory service had been for a period of 20 years;
                    or

subparagraph.content:
between the
                            appointed
                            day and his death;

he made an election under sections 3(1)(c)(ii) and
                        (2)(d)(ii) and 3A(4) which became effective on the date of his marriage;
                        or

has elected that the election referred to in subparagraph (i) shall be
                        effective on the first date referred to in section 3(2)(f)(ii);
                        or

the death of his spouse and the death or adoption by any other person
                        of any child of his who is under 23 years of
                        age;

paragraph.content:
the date any child in his period of dependency ceases to receive full-time
                    education at a university, college, school or other educational
                    establishment;

the date the child ceases to receive full-time education at a university,
                    college, school or other educational establishment within his period of
                    dependency;

in the case of a person who was such an officer at the
                        commencement* of this Ordinance,
                    within the period applicable under section 3(1)(a)(i);
